{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "FuelConsumption",
        "description": "Fuel consumption model: exponential decay of remaining fuel fraction F after ignition, per Eq. 3 of Mandel et al. (2011). Migrated from WildlandFire.jl src/level_set_fire_spread.jl:243 (`FuelConsumption` @component). The fuel-fraction ODE D(F) = -is_burning*F/T_f decays with time constant T_f when is_burning ≈ 1; the algebraic w0_effective = F*w0_initial feeds the FireHeatFlux component in the coupled WRF-SFIRE pipeline.",
        "tags": [
            "wildland_fire",
            "level_set",
            "fuel_consumption",
            "mandel2011"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "WildlandFire.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-r2s6)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Mandel, J., Beezley, J.D., and Kochanski, A.K. (2011). Coupled atmosphere-wildland fire modeling with WRF 3.3 and SFIRE 2011. Geosci. Model Dev., 4, 591–610. doi:10.5194/gmd-4-591-2011 — Equation 3 (fuel-fraction differential form) and §3.2 (fuel-load feedback)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "FuelConsumption": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Mandel, J., Beezley, J.D., and Kochanski, A.K. (2011). Coupled atmosphere-wildland fire modeling with WRF 3.3 and SFIRE 2011. Geosci. Model Dev., 4, 591–610. doi:10.5194/gmd-4-591-2011.",
                "notes": "source_ref: WildlandFire.jl:src/level_set_fire_spread.jl:243\nUpstream `FuelConsumption` is an MTK `@component` with two `@variables` — F(t)=1.0 (fuel fraction remaining) and w0_effective(t) (algebraic) — and three `@parameters` (T_f, w0_initial, is_burning=0.0). The two equations are preserved verbatim:\n  D(F) = -is_burning * F / T_f                 (Eq. 3, Mandel et al. 2011, differential form)\n  w0_effective = F * w0_initial                 (algebraic feedback to FireHeatFlux)\n\nIn the coupled WRF-SFIRE pipeline (couple2(LevelSetCoupler, FuelConsumptionCoupler) at coupling.jl:415), is_burning is driven by the level-set function via a smooth Heaviside is_burning = 0.5*(1 - tanh(ψ/ε_h)); when standalone, it stays a parameter and the user supplies a constant value. Likewise w0_initial and T_f are coupled from FuelModelLookup (coupling.jl:303) but default to free parameters here.\n\nAnalytical solution for constant is_burning: F(t) = exp(-is_burning*t/T_f); w0_effective(t) = w0_initial * exp(-is_burning*t/T_f). All inline tests below are evaluated against this closed form.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): linear constant-coefficient scalar ODE; SciPy LSODA truncation is far below 1e-6 over the tested horizons (≤1200 s, ≤30 e-folding times kept ≤3). Algebraic w0_effective inherits the same accuracy since it is a single multiply on F. Tests use the default tolerance throughout — no per-test loosening needed."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-6
            },
            "variables": {
                "T_f": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s",
                    "default": 119.0,
                    "description": "Fuel burn time constant (1/e decay time). Default 119 s ≈ 0.166 / 0.8514·166 (Anderson grass-fuel; T_f ≈ w / 0.8514·166 per Mandel et al. 2011)."
                },
                "w0_initial": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 0.166,
                    "description": "Initial oven-dry fuel load (Anderson 1982 fuel model 1 grass default)."
                },
                "is_burning": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Whether the fuel is burning (1=yes, 0=no, dimensionless). In the coupled level-set system this is driven by 0.5*(1 - tanh(ψ/ε_h))."
                },
                "F": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Fuel fraction remaining (1=full, 0=consumed)."
                },
                "w0_effective": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "description": "Effective fuel load after consumption — feeds FireHeatFlux."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["F"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    -1.0,
                                    "is_burning",
                                    "F"
                                ]
                            },
                            "T_f"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "w0_effective",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": ["F", "w0_initial"]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "no_burning_F_constant",
                    "description": "is_burning = 0 — fuel is unignited. The ODE collapses to D(F) = 0, so F stays at its initial value of 1.0 for all time. w0_effective = F·w0_initial stays at w0_initial. Sanity check that the multiplicative is_burning gate works.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "is_burning": 0.0,
                        "T_f": 119.0,
                        "w0_initial": 0.5
                    },
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "F": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1000.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 500.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 1000.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.5},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 1000.0, "expected": 0.5}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "anderson_grass_full_burn",
                    "description": "Anderson (1982) fuel model 1 grass parameters with is_burning=1: T_f=119 s, w0_initial=0.166 kg/m². Closed-form F(t)=exp(-t/119); w0_effective(t)=0.166·exp(-t/119). Sample at t=0 (F=1, w0_eff=0.166), t=119 (F=exp(-1), w0_eff=0.166·exp(-1)), t=238 (F=exp(-2), w0_eff=0.166·exp(-2)).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "is_burning": 1.0,
                        "T_f": 119.0,
                        "w0_initial": 0.166
                    },
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "F": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 238.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 119.0, "expected": 0.36787944117144233},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 238.0, "expected": 0.1353352832366127},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.166},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 119.0, "expected": 0.06106798723445943},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 238.0, "expected": 0.02246565701727771}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "partial_burning_state",
                    "description": "Partial burning (is_burning=0.5) with T_f=200, w0_initial=1.0. The effective decay constant is is_burning/T_f = 1/400, so F(t)=exp(-t/400). Sample at t=0, t=400 (F=exp(-1)), t=800 (F=exp(-2)). Verifies that is_burning enters the decay rate multiplicatively, not as a binary gate.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "is_burning": 0.5,
                        "T_f": 200.0,
                        "w0_initial": 1.0
                    },
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "F": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 800.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 400.0, "expected": 0.36787944117144233},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 800.0, "expected": 0.1353352832366127},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 400.0, "expected": 0.36787944117144233},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 800.0, "expected": 0.1353352832366127}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fast_burn_short_T_f",
                    "description": "Fast burn (T_f=10 s, is_burning=1, w0_initial=2.0): F drops to ~5% in three e-folding times. F(t)=exp(-t/10), w0_effective(t)=2·exp(-t/10). At t=10, F=exp(-1)≈0.368, w0_eff=2·exp(-1)≈0.736. At t=30, F=exp(-3)≈0.0498, w0_eff≈0.0996. Stress-test of the ODE integrator on a short-time-constant system.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "is_burning": 1.0,
                        "T_f": 10.0,
                        "w0_initial": 2.0
                    },
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "F": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 30.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 10.0, "expected": 0.36787944117144233},
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 30.0, "expected": 0.049787068367863944},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 10.0, "expected": 0.7357588823428847},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 30.0, "expected": 0.09957413673572789}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "w0_effective_product_identity",
                    "description": "Cross-check the product identity w0_effective ≡ F·w0_initial: pick is_burning=0.5, T_f=50, w0_initial=10.0, sample at t=50 where F=exp(-0.5·50/50)=exp(-0.5)≈0.6065 → w0_effective=6.0653. Verifies that the algebraic equation tracks the ODE state exactly (modulo float64 multiply roundoff).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "is_burning": 0.5,
                        "T_f": 50.0,
                        "w0_initial": 10.0
                    },
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "F": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 50.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F", "time": 50.0, "expected": 0.6065306597126334},
                        {"variable": "w0_effective", "time": 50.0, "expected": 6.065306597126334}
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "anderson_grass_decay_curve",
                    "description": "Anderson (1982) fuel model 1 grass: T_f=119 s, w0_initial=0.166 kg/m², continuous burning (is_burning=1). Reproduces the Mandel et al. (2011) Eq. 3 fuel-fraction decay curve over five e-folding times.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {
                            "F": 1.0
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "is_burning": 1.0,
                        "T_f": 119.0,
                        "w0_initial": 0.166
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 600.0},
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "F_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Fuel fraction remaining F(t) under continuous burning — exponential decay with T_f = 119 s.",
                            "x": {"variable": "t", "label": "time (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "F", "label": "F (fraction)"}
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "w0_effective_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Effective fuel load w0_effective(t) = F(t)·w0_initial — feeds the FireHeatFlux component.",
                            "x": {"variable": "t", "label": "time (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "w0_effective", "label": "w0_effective (kg/m²)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "is_burning_sweep",
                    "description": "Sweep is_burning from 0 to 1 at fixed T_f and w0_initial, sampling the smoothed Heaviside values that the LevelSetFireSpread coupling produces. Surfaces the linear scaling of the effective decay constant (is_burning/T_f) on the F(t) curve.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {
                            "F": 1.0
                        }
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "T_f": 119.0,
                        "w0_initial": 0.166
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 600.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "is_burning",
                                "range": {"start": 0.0, "stop": 1.0, "count": 6, "scale": "linear"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "F_curves_vs_is_burning",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Family of F(t) decay curves at varying burn-state values — illustrates the smooth-Heaviside coupling regime.",
                            "x": {"variable": "t", "label": "time (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "F", "label": "F (fraction)"}
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
